tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Most parameters are within normal limits. Notable findings include mildly elevated hemoglobin and markedly increased platelet distribution width, which may suggest underlying hematological changes; clinical correlation is advised. Urine specific gravity is slightly low, possibly indicating dilute urine or overhydration. No evidence of infection or renal dysfunction is seen. Recommend clinical correlation and follow-up if symptoms persist.
